							<tr>
								<td valign="top" align="left" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">
									<h2 style="font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:18px; line-height:22px; color:#888888; text-align:left; padding:0px 0 15px; margin:0px; font-weight: 700; mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">Dear Running Mad Challenger</h2>
									<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; color:#888888; mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">
									Thank you for your registering with Running Mad, we hope that you will enjoy the virtual races and the bling that comes along with it.</p>
									<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; color:#888888; mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">When you enter races, you will receive an email as a confirmation so that you can quickly access information about the challenge itself. If you haven’t received anything after entering a race then please do check you junk or spam folder.</p>
									<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; color:#888888; font-weight: 700; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">How does it work?</p>
									<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; color:#888888; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; padding-top: 5px; mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">If you are wondering how it works again then no problem. We want to keep things as simple as possible so that you can concentrate on getting the distance in.</p>
									<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; color:#888888; mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">Each medal will have a different challenge to meet, before you sign up all the information will be there for you to read.</p>
									<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; color:#888888; mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">The challenge is completed by getting the distance in. You can walk, jog, run, cycle, swim or even increasing your walks from not taking an elevator to walking down the stairs.</p>
									<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; color:#888888; mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">Once you have completed the challenge, pop back to our website at <a href="https://runningmad.co.uk">www.runningmad.co.uk</a> and click back on the race you entered and submit your evidence of the distance completed. You can include screen shots or pictures of your mobile phone fitness tracking, your smart watch running device or even a park run result where it includes your name.</p>
									<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; color:#888888; mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">We will at times use photos for social media purposes to give encouragement and motivation to others. If you don’t want us to publish any pictures then please do let us know.</p>
									<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; color:#888888; mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">Once you have submitted your evidence you will receive an email acknowledgement to say we have received your submission. It will take us upto 48 hours to validate your submission, once that is done you will receive an email advising you that your bling is on the way.</p>
									<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; color:#888888; mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">Once the Virtual Challenge is over, each medal will have a chosen charity or cause attached to it. It will detail before you enter, which charity we are supporting with this medal. So not only will you being motivated to run but you will be donating part of the sale of the race to a worthy cause.</p>
									<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; color:#888888; font-weight: 700; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">Data Protection</p>
									<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px; color:#888888; margin-top: 0px; padding-top: 5px; mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;">By entering, you agree that Running Mad may contact you by email or SMS. We will not pass on your details to any third parties but may contact you about new races.</p>
